Program: The History Hour
Title: Stopping The 'Shoe Bomber'
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswqml
Last Broadcast Date: Christmas Day 2018
Passenger Kwame James recalls how he helped overcome the British-born Richard Reid on American Airlines flight 63. Reid had hidden explosives in his shoe which failed to go off. Plus, the US apology for the internment of thousands of Japanese Americans in WW2, the first computer password, the woman who wrote Mary Poppins and a British theatrical group tours the Sahara. Photo: One of the shoes worn by Richard Reid on the American Airlines flight to Miami (ABC/Getty Images) Show less